The paper discusses the use of graphics cards as a stream processor for efficient computation, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper discusses the parallel processing capabilities of graphics cards. The use of graphics cards for image and video processing also makes cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of graphics cards for neural network computations, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of graphics cards as a co-processor for stream processing can be relevant to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
